column5: Up in the muskoka/algonquin region are they there yet?
I don't know, dammed if I'm driving that far, I've got a pile of blackflies here already, want to share a few.
Just make sure you bring a repellent with deet ,bugs hate it,go enjoy yourself,let us know how the fishing is!

Ya, that's what I thought, my parents aren't usually up for a weekend of camping with the flies "just to catch some trout". Still going for trout this weekend at the JW marriot though on lake rosseau.
We have them here in the kawartha's this week, but didn't have them in haliburton earlier this week. Anytime now they will be THICK!  S.
Fishing won't be very good if you got Deet on your hands,lol  Make sure to wash good before touching your lures/bait
Tuesdays weather will shut them down. There was lots of bug activity sunday. SKEETERS.
Getting attacked tonight in the garage installing the TrollMaster Pro2 on my Yamaha T8!  Of course I gotta wear shorts because it was nice out today, lol
